title: TravelBrands Granted Extension of Stay of Proceedings
text:
TravelBrands Granted Extension of Stay of Proceedings August 17, 2015 
Canadian travel and distribution network TravelBrands has been granted a second extension of the stay of proceedings from the Ontario Superior Court of Justice. The extension, which was granted under the Companies’ Creditors Arrangement Act, lasts until Sep. 30. TravelBrands was placed under creditor protector using the CAA back in May. According to a statement from the company, it has made “significant progress in the discussions with its landlord at 75 Eglinton and is optimistic that it will be able to reach a mutually agreeable form of the settlement agreement in the near term.” 0
